[2] Cholera - Uganda
Date: Fri, 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and New Vision (Kampala)[edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200611030097.html>

Cholera has spread in Rakai district with 6 deaths and 20 people
admitted in hospital. District director of health services Dr.
Robert Mayanja said tests by the Central Laboratory in Kampala
confirmed it was cholera.
Opening a health workshop at Rakai district headquarters on Mon, 30
Oct 2006, Mayanja said cholera is caused by eating food contaminated
with human waste.
Mayanja said the epidemic had spread from Rakai town council and
Byakabanda sub-county to the neighboring sub-county of Kifamba.
[Byline: Ali Mambule]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Rakia district of Uganda borders Lake Victoria to the district's
east and borders Tanzania to the south. It can be found on a map of
Uganda at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf>. - Mod.LL]
