[4] Cholera - Kenya (Mombasa)
Date: Fri, 27 Oct 2006
From: SK Sharif <sksharif@ikenya.com>

The Ministry of Health has confirmed an outbreak of cholera in
Mombasa, Kenya. A total of 14 cases with 1 death have been reported.
The index case was an 18-month-old child who died on 21 Oct 2006.
The first 6 cases were from the same family. Stool samples were
positive for _Vibrio cholerae_ serotype Ogawa. The outbreak came
after heavy rainfall in the Coast especially in Mombasa and Kilifi
Districts which led to flooding.
An outbreak of cholera was reported from Vanga village in Kwale
District in 16 Sep 2006 and so far 81 cases have been reported with 3
deaths. Coast Province has had heavy rains in the last 3 weeks
leading to floods and landslides. About 13 people have lost their
lives due to floods and landslides.
--
Dr S K Sharif
Ministry of Health, Kenya
<sksharif@ikenya.com>
[ProMED again thanks Dr. Sharif for this report. Mombasa, as Kwale
District, is in the Coast Province which can be found in southeastern
Kenya at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/kenya.pdf>. - Mod.LL]
